      <h3>Dangerous Wild Life</h3>
      <h1>Asian Giant Hornet</h1>
      <img src="/giant_hornet.jpg" alt="asian_hornet" class="smaller-image">
      <p>The Asian giant hornet (Vespa mandarinia) is a formidable insect found in various parts of China, it can grow up to two inches in length. Despite known not to be aggresive towards human, There were cases of it and the sting itself generate quite painful experience.

      </p>
    <a href="#" class="read-more">Read Full Post</a>
    <div class="full-content">
      <p>These hornets are known to be active during the warmer months and are most commonly found in rural and forested areas.
          Staying calm and moving slowly in the situation of encounter could really help you get out of it. Do no hit or swat the hornet as it will activate their defense mechanism.
          If you have been stung by it, seek medical help as soon as possible as it could cause severe allergic reaction.

      </p>
