  <h3>Natural Disasters</h3>
  <h1>Floods</h1>
      <img src="/floodChina.jpg" alt="flood" class="smaller-image">
      <p> China is prone to both river and coastal flooding due to its diverse geography, including vast river systems and extensive coastlines. Several factors contribute to the prevalence of flooding in the country, including heavy monsoon rains, rapid urbanization, deforestation, and topography that can lead to river blockages. 
        China has invested in various flood control and mitigation measures, such as building dams, levees, and reservoirs. However, despite these efforts, flooding remains a significant challenge, impacting both rural and urban areas and causing displacement, property damage, and loss of life.       
      </p>

    <a href="#" class="read-more">Read Full Post</a>
    <div class="full-content">
      <p> Keep track of weather forecasts, flood alerts, and warnings issued by local authorities through news sources, radio, or weather apps. It is also important to create a just-in-case plan to counter the flood. 
          During a flood it is advised to move to higher sturdy ground. Do not try to walk through floodwater because we may not know the depth of it. Staying informed of the next action to do is important in the event of flood.
          After the flood remember to disinfect everything as floodwater could carry lots of bacteria and virus. Seek professional help if required. 


      </p>
    </div>
    <h1>Earthquakes</h1>
        <img src="/earthquakeChina.jpg" alt="earthquake" class="smaller-image">
      <p> China is located in a seismically active region due to its location near the boundary of the Eurasian and Indian tectonic plates. This geological setting makes the country prone to experiencing earthquakes of varying magnitudes.
        One of the most devastating earthquakes in recent memory was the 2008 Sichuan earthquake, also known as the Wenchuan earthquake, which had a magnitude of 7.9. This earthquake caused widespread destruction and led to significant humanitarian efforts to aid the affected regions.

      </p>
    <a href="#" class="read-more">Read Full Post</a>
    <div class="full-content">
      <p>
         It is important to secure the nearby furniture if possible as it will decrease the chance of it falling to you during an earthquake. Make sure to check the safe spot incase of the event, and do a practice drill.
         Do not panic in the event of earthquake, stay calm and evacuate if possible. if not, go under a sturdy desk or table and avoid windows.
      </p>
    </div>
